    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All three QoIs satisfy quantitative acceptance criteria (percent difference < 10%; E/uval < 1.96). Twelve of thirteen credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The single shortfall (Test conditions, achieved 1 vs. required 2) is accepted given the prescriptive ASTM F1717 protocol and the medium model risk level. Aleatory uncertainty from specimen-to-specimen variation is discussed in the validation report narrative and is reflected in the experimental uncertainty band used to compute E/uval. The overall credibility evidence is sufficient to support the Accepted decision at Medium assurance level.",
